  "prompt": "What do I do when I have a feeling my live-in girlfriend is cheating on me?",
  "response": "Dealing with the suspicion that a partner might be cheating can be incredibly distressing. Here are some steps you can take to address your feelings and the situation:\n\n1. **Reflect on Your Feelings**:\n   - Take some time to understand why you feel this way. Are there specific behaviors or changes that have led you to suspect infidelity?\n\n2. **Gather Evidence**:\n   - Before jumping to conclusions, try to gather some evidence to support your suspicion. This doesn't mean invading your partner's privacy but being observant about changes in behavior, patterns, and communication.\n\n3. **Communicate**:\n   - Have an honest and calm conversation with your girlfriend. Express your feelings without sounding accusatory. Use \"I\" statements to communicate how certain behaviors make you feel.\n   - For example, \"I feel worried about our relationship because of some recent changes I've noticed.\"\n\n4. **Listen**:\n   - Give her a chance to respond and explain her perspective. It's important to listen actively to understand her side of the story.\n\n5. **Seek Professional Help**:\n   - If communication proves difficult or if there's a lot of tension, consider talking to a relationship counselor. They can provide a neutral ground for discussing issues and improving communication.\n\n6. **Self-Care**:\n   - Look after your own mental and emotional well-being. Practice self-care activities that help you manage stress and clarify your feelings.\n\n7. **Evaluate the Relationship**:\n   - If the suspicion is confirmed or if trust cannot be rebuilt, consider the future of the relationship. It's important to be in a relationship where both partners feel secure and valued.\n\nWhatever you choose to do, prioritize respectful communication and your well-being.",
